  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/8896758/initial-size-for-the-arraylist",
  "title" : "Initial size for the ArrayList",
  "body" : "<p>You can set the initial size for an ArrayList by doing</p>\n\n<pre><code>ArrayList&lt;Integer&gt; arr=new ArrayList&lt;Integer&gt;(10);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>However, you can't do</p>\n\n<pre><code>arr.add(5, 10);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>because it causes an out of bounds exception.</p>\n\n<p>What is the use of setting an initial size if you can't access the space you allocated?</p>\n\n<p>The add function is defined as <code>add(int index, Object element)</code> so I am not adding to index 10.</p>\n"
}